*My Linux/Unix dotfiles*

*How to install
Clone the repository into your home directory
Install GNU Stow
Arch Linux and it's derivatives:
```sudo pacman -S stow```
Debian/Ubuntu
```sudo apt-get install stow```
Stow the specific application config files you want
```stow bspwm
   stow sxhkd
   stow termite```
For specific rices/themes that you want to install, use the following syntax
```stow -d $INSTALL_DIR_HERE/Dotfiles/rice-or-theme-name```

List of current themes in repository
* warm-n-comfy

If you have any issues installing, please open an issue in github
